OL,3,CWhat is a 'super plume' summer which
OL,4,Ccould push temperatures to 40C?
OL,6,FSummer temperatures usually rise due
OL,7,Fto day-on-day heating (known as
OL,8,Fhomegrown warmth) as high pressure
OL,9,Ftakes charge.
OL,11,FThis was the case through the middle
OL,12,Fof last week.
OL,14,FWe also see temperatures climb easily
OL,15,Fwhen we draw in hotter, usually humid,
OL,16,Fair from Europe in a southerly airflow.
OL,18,FThis is the scenario we expect by
OL,19,FSunday and Monday, when a plume of hot
OL,20,Fair surges north into the UK and
OL,21,Ftemperatures rise easily and rapidly.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
